Mr Wade, 63, from Longview, Texas, said: 'When I told people I was going to build the Oval Office I don't think they realised that it was going to be exactly the same as the one the president sits in everyday.

'But it's identical down to the last detail.

'I had George W Bush look at a blow-up photo of my Oval Office and he said "you've got it down, everything is just right."

Now Mr Wade gives tours of his collection, which includes JFK's former car and rocking chair and a dresser bought by Calvin Coolidge.

